Package io.github.thepieterdc.random

Interface RandomGenerator<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type class of the generated value
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRandomGenerator, RandomBooleanGenerator, RandomCollectionGenerator, RandomDoubleGenerator, RandomFloatGenerator, RandomIntegerGenerator, RandomLongGenerator, RandomLowercaseLetterGenerator, RandomObjectGenerator, RandomPrimeGenerator, RandomStringGenerator, RandomTimeGenerator, RandomUppercaseLetterGenerator
    public interface RandomGenerator<T>
    A generator for random values.

    • Method Detail

      • generate

        Collection<T> generate​(int amount,
                       int maxTries)
        Tries to generates {amount} unique random values within the given maximum amount of attempts (this serves as a bound to prevent endless loops).
        Parameters:
        amount - the amount of random values to generate, must be lower than or equal to the capacity
        maxTries - the maximum amount of tries allowed
        Returns:
        at most {amount} unique random values

      • generate

        T generate()
        Generates a random value.
        Returns:
        the random value

      • getCapacity

        long getCapacity()
        Gets the maximum amount of unique random values that can be generated by this random generator.
        Returns:
        the maximum amount of distinct random values

      • getIntegerCapacity

        int getIntegerCapacity()
        Gets the maximum amount of unique random values that can be generated by this random generator. This must be an int, since it might be used in collections.
        Returns:
        a lower bound for the maximum amount of distinct random values
